1. Vector Fields
- Get a box.
- Put yourâ€¦ points in that box. As in, randomly scatter points in the box. Lots of them.
- Apply the noise of your choice to the normals of those points.
- Transfer that normal directions to a volume, but rename the normal attribute to velocity.
- Bring the volume into a dopnet as a fluidsource.
- Export the result of the dopnet with the FGA Exporter OTL from Orbolt.
